\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} when $c=3$. ||| We start by substituting $c=3$ into the expression: $\left(3^3 - 3(3-1)^3\right)^3$. The value of $(3-1)^3$ calculates to $2^3 = 6$, so our expression is $\left(3^3 - 3 \cdot 6\right)^3$. Next, we evaluate $3^3 = 27$ and get $3 \cdot 6 = 18$. This simplifies our expression to $\left(27 - 18\right)^3$, giving us $\left(9\right)^3$. Therefore, the final answer is $\boxed{729}$.

