Note that when we say the grid is 5 by 5 we mean that each row and column contains 5 dots! ||| To find the side length of square ABCD, we can use the distance between points A and D. The coordinates for A (3, 4) and D (0, 3) give us the side length as $AD = |3 - 0| + |4 - 3| = 3 + 1 = 4$ cm. Thus, the area of the square is $4^2 = 16$ cm$^2$, and the perimeter is $4 \times 4 = 16$ cm. The product of the area and perimeter is $16 \text{ cm}^2 \times 16 \text{ cm} = 256 \text{ cm}^3$. Therefore, the final answer is \boxed{256}.

